<doc id="1032820" wikidata="Q22074520" url="?curid=1032820" title="Laughing Gas (film)">
<text>Laughing Gas is the title of several American short films (1907, 1914 starring Charlie Chaplin, 1915, 1920) whose plot revolves around real or would-be dentists.

==1907 film==
===Plot===
The plot is that of a black woman going to the dentist for a toothache and being given laughing gas. On her way walking home, and in other situations, she can&#x27;t stop laughing, and everyone she meets &quot;catches&quot; the laughter from her, including a vendor and police officers.

===Cast===
*Edward Boulden
*Mr. La Montte
*Bertha Regustus ... Mandy Brown
*Mr. Sullivan

==1914 film==
==1915 film==
===Cast===
*Jimmy Aubrey ... Heinie
*Walter Kendig ... Louie

==1920 film==
A film directed by Tom Buckingham.

==References==
