<doc id="1032933" wikidata="Q4976230" url="?curid=1032933" title="Brown Peak (Kern County, California)">
<text>Brown Peak is a peak located in Kern County, California. The peak is located on King Solomons Ridge at the head of Haight Canyon, southwest of Liebel Peak and north of Loraine, California in Sequoia National Forest.

Brown Peak is named for Charlie Brown, a miner who lived in the area during the early 1900s.

